http://www.thehindu.com/news/cities/mumbai/news/Patrolling-van-overturns-10-cops-hurt/article13991090.ece

A police patrolling vehicle overturned near Uttan in Thane district early on Saturday morning. Officials said all 10 policemen in the vehicle sustained minor injuries in the incident.According to police officials, the patrolling van, attached to the Zone XI of the Mumbai Police, was tasked with patrolling Gorai beach from Friday night to Saturday morning. After completing their shift, they were on their way back to the Zone XI office in Borivali when the accident occurred at 6:30 am. “The 10 personnel in the van sustained injuries. None of them were seriously injured,” said DCP Vikram Deshmane, Zone XI.